oai_dc:dc.dc:title: New grassed waterway
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Young, H.J., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: W.L. Clement, WUC, shown in grass waterway vegetated with fescue and ladino clover and constructed and seeded in fall of 1960. 6 mi. s. of Woodbury.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
